| Component          | Namespace   | Type       |
| ------------------ | ----------- | ---------- |
| CoreDNS            | kube-system | Deployment |
| kube-proxy         | kube-system | DaemonSet  |
| vpc-cni (aws-node) | kube-system | DaemonSet  |

-----------------------------------------------------------------
1. CoreDNS:

What: DNS server for Kubernetes
Purpose: Service discovery inside cluster

Pod wants to reach mysql-service:
        ↓
CoreDNS resolves name to IP
mysql-service.default.svc.cluster.local
        ↓
Returns ClusterIP ✅
Pod connects ✅

Without CoreDNS:
  Pods cannot find each other ❌
  Service names don't work ❌
  Must use IPs directly ❌
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. kube-proxy:

What: Network proxy on every node
Purpose: Routes traffic to correct pods

Request hits Service ClusterIP:
        ↓
kube-proxy intercepts
        ↓
Checks iptables rules
        ↓
Forwards to correct pod IP ✅

Without kube-proxy:
  Services don't work ❌
  Traffic cannot reach pods ❌
  LoadBalancer won't work ❌
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. VPC CNI:

What: Container Network Interface for AWS
Purpose: Gives pods real AWS VPC IP addresses

Pod created:
        ↓
VPC CNI assigns real VPC IP
e.g. 10.0.1.25 ✅
        ↓
Pod can communicate directly
with other AWS services ✅
RDS, ElastiCache, EC2 ✅

Without VPC CNI:
  Pods get fake IPs ❌
  Cannot talk to AWS services directly ❌
  No VPC level networking ❌
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

How they work together:

Pod A wants to reach Service B:

1. Pod A asks CoreDNS           ← DNS resolution
        ↓
2. CoreDNS returns ClusterIP
        ↓
3. kube-proxy routes traffic    ← traffic routing
        ↓
4. VPC CNI delivers packet      ← network delivery
   to correct pod IP ✅
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Simple one liner each:

Addon        | One liner
-----------------------------------------------
CoreDNS      | DNS — finds services by name
kube-proxy   | Routing — sends traffic to right pod
VPC CNI      | Networking — gives pods real AWS VPC IPs
